name: dump_active_ciphers
description: - This simple sample shows the ciphers that are currently available to Java, and whether or not they're enabled or disabled. - This can be used in conjunction with making changes to the `java.security` file's `jdk.tls.disabledAlgorithms` config entry. - We'll use this to verify that ciphers that should be disabled have actually been disabled. - The java sample was [snagged from here](https://confluence.atlassian.com/stashkb/list-ciphers-used-by-jvm-679609085.html) and slightly modified.
